
To open jar files in kali linux 2.0 create a empty text file with the extension desktop (such as test.desktop) , and paste the following content into it.

[Desktop Entry]
Name=Java
Comment=Java
GenericName=Java
Keywords=java
Exec=java -jar %f
Terminal=false
X-MultipleArgs=false
Type=Application
MimeType=application/x-java-archive
StartupNotify=true

Then save the file and move or copy the file in /usr/share/applications folder.
now change the 'open_with' application with 'java' from the list.

source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ays_IOKclZo
